olive oil
2 clove garlic
20 g butter
1 packet jasmine rice
1.25 cup water (for the rice)
1 carrot
1 packet green beans
1 packet Asian Greens
1 packet beef strips
1 packet hoisin sauce
½ tbs soy sauce
1 tsp brown sugar
¼ cup water (for the sauce)
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
2 tsp plain flour
1 sachet Crispy Shallots

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, heat the butter with a dash of olive oil over medium heat.
• Cook garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Add jasmine rice, the water (for the rice) and a generous pinch of salt, stir, then bring to the boil.
• Reduce heat to low and cover with a lid. Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and all the water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, thinly slice carrot into half-moons. Trim green beans and cut into thirds.
• Roughly chop Asian greens.
• In a small bowl, combine hoisin sauce, soy sauce, brown sugar, and the water (for the sauce). Set aside.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook carrot and green beans, tossing, until softened, 3-4 minutes.
• Add Asian greens and a dash of water. Cook until just wilted, 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• In a medium bowl, add beef strips, sweet soy seasoning and the plain flour. Season with salt and pepper, then gently toss until well coated.
• Return the frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips, tossing, in batches until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• Add the veggies and hoisin mixture to the tofu, tossing, until heated through, 1 minute.

• Divide garlic rice between bowls.
• Top with hoisin beef and veggie stir-fry.
• Garnish with the crispy shallots. Enjoy!